The paper deals with the problem of designing maximum distance separable (MDS) codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also presents an algebraic-combinatorial approach for proving a conjecture related to MDS codes, which involves polynomial-degree reduction and Wronskian determinants, indicating a connection to computer science theory (cs.DS, cs.CC). The paper also involves some algebraic and combinatorial techniques, which are relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and control theory (cs.SY).
